{"word":"ληπτέος","slug":"ληπτέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ληπτέος</b></el> <el>(ληπτέος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:λαμβάνω'><el>λαμβάνω</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be taken</i> or <i>accepted</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <el>ληπτέον</el>, <i>one must take hold</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>: <i>one must undertake</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <i>one must take</i> or <i>choose</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>one must take, receive</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}